167: ## Do's and Don'ts
168: 
169: ### Do
170: - Use #f9a600 (Amber Signal) as the ONLY filled chromatic button background — no other color gets a fill button treatment
171: - Set all text in Interphases Pro Variable (or Inter Variable substitute) at the defined weight stops: 400 for body, 492 for emphasis and buttons, 584 for headings and display
172: - Use Espresso (#261b07) for all primary text and icons — never use true #000000; the warm undertone is part of the brand
173: - Apply warm-tinted shadows (brown rgba 0.149, 0.106, 0.027) at 6% opacity with 0px 4px 8px spread — never use cool gray shadows
174: - Use 8px radius for all cards, buttons, and nav elements; reserve 4px for badges and tags; never use fully rounded pill shapes except for status indicators
175: - Set headlines at the tight tracking values from the type scale (e.g. -1.58px at 72px, -0.31px at 24px) — the negative letter-spacing is what makes display type feel set rather than typed
176: - Layer surfaces as Cream Canvas → Pure Paper → elevated white with shadow, using Linen (#e3dfd5) borders for separation rather than background color shifts
177: 
178: ### Don't
179: - Do not introduce blue, green, red, or purple as interface colors — the only chromatic hues are amber (#f9a600, #e89b01) and warm accents (terracotta, honey, wisteria)
180: - Do not use #000000 for text or backgrounds — Espresso (#261b07) maintains the warm paper quality
181: - Do not apply shadows with cool gray tints — all shadows must use the warm brown base (srgb 0.149, 0.106, 0.027)
182: - Do not use filled buttons in any color other than Amber Signal for primary actions — secondary actions are ghost/outlined only
183: - Do not set body type at weight 700 or above — the custom font's weight 584 is the maximum semibold, and weight 492 serves as medium
184: - Do not use line-heights above 1.25 for any text — the system is tight and dense, not airy
185: - Do not separate sections with colored background bands — transition via whitespace and Linen dividers on the continuous Cream Canvas
