170: ## Do's and Don'ts
171: 
172: ### Do
173: - Use 9999px radius for every button, input, and interactive pill — the pill shape is the signature
174: - Pair Sharp Grotesk Bold 900 with Harriet Display 300 in the same headline for the signature mixed-weight effect
175: - Set page background to #f7f2ff and hero background to #beaaff — never pure white as the dominant canvas
176: - Apply the 48px radius to cards and large containers, reserving 9999px for interactive elements
177: - Use #2c232 for primary text and filled buttons — its violet undertone keeps it on-palette against lavender
178: - Break sections into full-bleed color bands that transition from cool violet to warm cream toward the footer
179: - Anchor the color story with #f97316 only on the Bitcoin currency icon — it is the sole warm accent
180: 
181: ### Don't
182: - Do not use standard banking blue, green, or neutral gray as a brand color — it breaks the lavender identity
183: - Do not apply heavy drop shadows — the system relies on surface color contrast, not elevation, for depth
184: - Do not mix the Sharp Grotesk 900 and Harriet 300 at the same size — the contrast is in their weight difference at different sizes
185: - Do not use border-radius values between 8px and 48px on primary surfaces — the system jumps from pill to soft-card
186: - Do not place more than one filled chromatic button per section — the dark pill is the only primary action
187: - Do not use stock photography or 3D renders — the visual language is flat editorial illustration on lavender
188: - Do not set body type below 16px in Inter — the 14–16px floor preserves the spacious, magazine-like feel
