164: ## Do's and Don'ts
165: 
166: ### Do
167: - Use PP Neue Corp Compact at 48px or larger for any heading that needs to feel structural — below 40px the ultrabold weight overwhelms and loses its industrial character
168: - Apply 40px border-radius to all cards, content blocks, and non-pill buttons as the default surface radius
169: - Use 800px border-radius (full pill) for all buttons, tags, nav containers, and small interactive elements
170: - Set primary CTAs to Ember (#fc5000) with Obsidian (#070607) text, sized at 12px/24px padding — never rectangular, always pill-shaped
171: - Keep body text at DM Sans 500 (Medium) — never drop to Regular weight, which reads as anemic against the ultrabold display type
172: - Use the halftone dot pattern (orange dots on violet) as the hero/signature visual treatment — it is the system’s most recognizable motif
173: - Layer surfaces using color contrast (Pumice canvas → Limestone cards → Ember features) rather than shadows or borders
174: 
175: ### Don't
176: - Do not add drop shadows to any element — the system is intentionally flat; shadows would undermine the paper-like warmth
177: - Do not use rectangular (low-radius) buttons — the pill/40px-radius treatment is non-negotiable
178: - Do not introduce additional accent colors beyond Ember, Plasma Violet, and Sulfur — the palette is deliberately constrained to three chromatic tones
179: - Do not use Regular or Bold weights of DM Sans for body — Medium (500) is the only correct weight
180: - Do not set headings below 26px or above 189px — the display type only works at architectural scale
181: - Do not use Plasma Violet for buttons or controls — it is reserved for the hero halftone and a single accent card
182: - Do not apply negative letter-spacing to PP Neue Corp Compact — the +0.02em positive tracking is intentional at display sizes to prevent stroke collision
